OL,3,CHarvard removes human skin from
OL,4,Cbinding of 19th century book
OL,6,FHarvard University said it has removed
OL,7,Fhuman skin from the binding of a 19th
OL,8,Fcentury book about the afterlife that
OL,9,Fhas been in its collections since the
OL,10,F1930s.
OL,12,FThe decision came after a review found
OL,13,Fethical concerns with the book's
OL,14,Forigin and history.
OL,16,FThe book, Des Destinees de L'ame,
OL,17,Fmeaning "Destinies of the Soul," was
OL,18,Fwritten by Arsene Houssaye, a French
OL,19,Fnovelist and poet, in the early 1880s.
