OL,3,CHarvard removes human skin from
OL,4,Cbinding of 19th century book
OL,6,FThe printed text was given to a
OL,7,Fphysician, Ludovic Bouland, who "bound
OL,8,Fthe book with skin he took without
OL,9,Fconsent from the body of a deceased
OL,10,Ffemale patient in a hospital where he
OL,11,Fworked," Harvard said in a recent
OL,12,Fstatement.
OL,14,FThe book has been at the university's
OL,15,FHoughton Library and had included a
OL,16,Fhandwritten note from Bouland inside
OL,17,Fthe book.
