OL,3,CHarvard removes human skin from
OL,4,Cbinding of 19th century book
OL,6,F"Library lore suggests that decades
OL,7,Fago, students employed to page
OL,8,Fcollections in Houghton's stacks were
OL,9,Fhazed by being asked to retrieve the
OL,10,Fbook without being told it included
OL,11,Fhuman remains."
OL,13,FWhen the testing confirmed the book
OL,14,Fwas bound by human skin, "the library
OL,15,Fpublished posts on the Houghton blog
OL,16,Fthat utilized a sensationalistic,
OL,17,Fmorbid, and humorous tone that fueled
OL,18,Fsimilar international media coverage,"
OL,19,Fthe university said in its statement.
