OL,3,CHarvard removes human skin from
OL,4,Cbinding of 19th century book
OL,6,FThe removed skin is now in "secure
OL,7,Fstorage at Harvard Library," Anne-
OL,8,FMarie Eze, Houghton Library associate
OL,9,Flibrarian, said in the question-and-
OL,10,Fanswer session.
OL,12,FThe library said it will be conducting
OL,13,Fadditional research into the book,
OL,14,FBouland and the anonymous female
OL,15,Fpatient.
OL,17,FIt is also working with French
OL,18,Fauthorities to determine a "final
OL,19,Frespectful disposition."
